abstract: An analysis of how top-tier Republicans seeking the White House spent November reveals that a strenuous itinerary does not necessarily translate to robust poll numbers.
snippet: An analysis of how top-tier Republicans seeking the White House spent November reveals that a strenuous itinerary does not necessarily translate to robust poll numbers.
lead_paragraph: Donald J. Trump mocks his opponents as “low energy,” but his own campaign travel schedule is relatively sleepy: He left his home base of New York for only 17 public events during a 30-day stretch.

abstract: The bipartisan legislation, which is expected to pass, falls short of critics’ demands for stronger measures against suspected currency manipulation by other countries.
snippet: The bipartisan legislation, which is expected to pass, falls short of critics’ demands for stronger measures against suspected currency manipulation by other countries.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House is expected to approve bipartisan trade and customs legislation on Friday that would empower the administration to more forcefully counter unfair trading practices, though the measure’s provisions against suspected currency manipulation by other countries fell short of demands from critics in both parties.

abstract: An analysis of 95,000 words Mr. Trump said in public in the past week reveals powerful patterns in his speech which, historians say, echo the appeals of demagogues of the past century.
snippet: An analysis of 95,000 words Mr. Trump said in public in the past week reveals powerful patterns in his speech which, historians say, echo the appeals of demagogues of the past century.
lead_paragraph: “Something bad is happening,” Donald J. Trump warned New Hampshire voters Tuesday night, casting suspicions on Muslims and mosques. “Something really dangerous is going on.”

abstract: Sting, Sutton Foster, Bernadette Peters and others sang at the show, which was hosted by Seth MacFarlane.
snippet: Sting, Sutton Foster, Bernadette Peters and others sang at the show, which was hosted by Seth MacFarlane.
lead_paragraph: Everything that was good and bad about Lincoln Center’s underwhelming fund-raising gala timed to Frank Sinatra’s centennial, “Sinatra: Voice for a Century” at David Geffen Hall on Thursday, converged late in the evening in a moment of disturbing clarity. As the mighty New York Philharmonic orchestra, conducted by Alan Gilbert, played the funereal opening chords from Nelson Riddle’s original arrangement of “What’s New?” from the 1958 album, “Frank Sinatra Sings for Only the Lonely,” an emotional chasm opened up.

abstract: For people who have grown cynical about self-help, new books teach you how to toughen up, ignore the haters and know your league. Brace yourself.
snippet: For people who have grown cynical about self-help, new books teach you how to toughen up, ignore the haters and know your league. Brace yourself.
lead_paragraph: There’s no data on this, but I’d guess that most self-help books are purchased in the depths of a bad mood. When we’re happy, we idle and play. When we’re not, we buy books that promise a fix. And when those books fail to deliver, we feel wronged. The market has responded accordingly, with a crop of new books seemingly aimed at people who have grown cynical about self-help. These books have profane titles, saucy premises and, in one case, a cover photo of the author posing nearly nude and oiled and aiming a weapon. Their tone is belligerent. Much like their intended readers, these books could be credibly described as having an attitude problem.

abstract: A day after 14 colleagues in a county health department were murdered at their office, family and friends tried to make sense of a devastating loss.
snippet: A day after 14 colleagues in a county health department were murdered at their office, family and friends tried to make sense of a devastating loss.
lead_paragraph: Struck down at an office holiday party, almost all the victims of the mass shooting Wednesday in San Bernardino, Calif., were friends and colleagues. And in a notable difference from some other highly publicized rampages, some of them also knew their killer, Syed Rizwan Farook, who opened fire on the group with his wife, Tashfeen Malik, the authorities said.
